  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. Expanding the left side: (cx + 2)(4x\u00b2 \u2212 dx + 5) = 4cx\u00b3 \u2212 cdx\u00b2 + 5cx + 8x\u00b2 \u2212 2dx + 10 = 4cx\u00b3 + (8 \u2212 cd)x\u00b2 + (5c \u2212 2d)x + 10. Equating the coefficient of x\u00b2 on each side: 8 \u2212 cd = \u221210, so cd = 18.</p><p>The other choices result from sign errors in matching coefficients.</p>",
